{{Infobox Painting | image_file=William-Adolphe Bouguereau (1825-1905) - A Dream of Spring (1901).jpg | title=Rêve de printemps | artist=[[William-Adolphe Bouguereau]] | image_size=280px | year=1901 | medium=[[Oil painting|Oil on canvas]] | museum=[[Indianapolis Museum of Art]] | height_imperial = 73 | width_imperial = 50 }}
'''''Rêve de printemps''''' ([[English language|en.]] ''Dream of Spring'') is a 1901 [[painting]] by [[William-Adolphe Bouguereau]]. The [[painting]] is an [[allegory]] of [[Spring (season)|spring]], it shows a young [[woman]] sitting in a [[forest]] surrounded by three small [[Cupid|amores]] who crown her with a [[wreath]] of spring [[flower]]s as ''[[Flora (mythology)|déesse du printemps]]''.<ref name="ima">[http://www.imamuseum.org/collections/artwork/dream-spring-r%C3%AAve-de-printemps-bouguereau-william-adolphe Dream of Spring (Rêve de printemps), Bouguereau, William-Adolphe], Indianapolis Museum of Art, www.imamuseum.org</ref><ref name="artdaily">[http://artdaily.com/news/62932/Indianapolis-Museum-of-Art-receives-major-painting-by-William-Adolphe-Bouguereau#.VBIyEhZgDW4 Indianapolis Museum of Art receives major painting by William-Adolphe Bouguereau], artdaily.com</ref>
